<%= link_to "", "", :id => "about" %>
<div id="about_wrapper">
  <div id="about_container">
    <h1>ABOUT ME</h1>
    <h2>Nice to meet you.</h2>

    <div id="about_module_container">
      <%= image_tag "about.jpg", :alt => "About Me", :id => "img_about" %>

      The first website I ever built was Awesome with a capital <i>A</i>, and I loved it. At the time, it was hard for me to imagine anything better than creating and living in my own little world, complete with frames, blinking text, animated GIF's, and (wait for it) background music. In retrospect, I can't argue that the site was completely and utterly horrendous, but I was really proud of it in tenth grade.

      <p><i>That was then.</i></p>

      <p>Years later, some things have changed -- I no longer use blinking text and neither should you; while other things have not -- I'm still deeply passionate about technology.</p>

      <p>This passion, combined with a bit of luck and a fortuitous series of events, eventually led to the beginning of my career in northern California's San Francisco Bay Area, a globally recognized epicenter of digital innovation.</p>

      <p>Throughout the course of my development as a now seasoned Internet professional, I've continued to refine a <%= link_to "uniquely multi-faceted skill set", "#skills", :class => "scroll" %> that has and will enable me to play key roles in the growth of both start-ups and publicly traded companies.</p>

      <p>My priority is to work in intensely collaborative environments with high-performing, highly respectful individuals who pride themselves on their integrity and embrace the level of commitment needed to win.</p>

      <p>I am currently available for hire. Please click <%= link_to "here", "#hire", :class => "scroll" %> for details on how to contact me.</p>
    </div> <!-- end module_container -->
  </div> <!-- end about_container -->
</div> <!-- end about_wrapper -->

